<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="23">
9. 
<taxonomicName LSID="76E3477F-9753-5544-A9EF-9EE2BA9CBE52" authority="A. R. Sm. &amp; Lorence" authorityName="A. R. Sm. &amp; Lorence" authorityYear="2011" class="Filicopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Cyclosorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclosorus castaneus" order="Polypodiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="castaneus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="(Sphaerostephanos)">Cyclosorus (Sphaerostephanos) castaneus A. R. Sm. &amp; Lorence</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="23">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Cyclosorus castaneus A. R. Sm. &amp; Lorence. A frond B upper surface of pinna C lower surface of fertile pinnules showing sori, hairs, and glands D detail of lower surface of fertile pinnule with sorus, hairs, and glands. Drawn from the type collection (Lorence et al. 6115)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/9907" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
